From: johnsonfarmsus
Subject: [PATCH] ml/device: respect parent env ROCR_VISIBLE_DEVICES

updateVisibleDevicesEnv builds extraEnvs for the model-load runner using the
chosen device's FilterID. If the parent process (Ollama main, started from
systemd) already pre-filtered with ROCR_VISIBLE_DEVICES=N, the chosen device
in Ollama's view has been re-indexed to FilterID=0. Setting
ROCR_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0 in the spawned runner — which has a fresh,
unfiltered view — points it at physical device 0, which is the WRONG GPU
on systems where the user intentionally pinned to a non-zero index.

When the parent env already pins ROCR_VISIBLE_DEVICES, leave it alone.
Ollama's per-process filtering is a no-op on top of the parent's pin.

---
 ml/device.go | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/ml/device.go b/ml/device.go
--- a/ml/device.go
+++ b/ml/device.go
@@ -1,6 +1,7 @@
 package ml

 import (
+	"os"
 	"context"
 	"encoding/binary"
 	"encoding/json"
@@ -576,6 +577,12 @@ func (d DeviceInfo) updateVisibleDevicesEnv(env map[string]string, mustFilter bo
 		if runtime.GOOS != "linux" {
 			envVar = "HIP_VISIBLE_DEVICES"
 		}
+		// Respect a systemd-set ROCR_VISIBLE_DEVICES from parent env.
+		// Overriding with the post-filter FilterID re-indexes and would point
+		// the model-load runner at the wrong physical device.
+		if os.Getenv(envVar) != "" {
+			return
+		}
 	case "CUDA":
 		if !mustFilter {
 			// By default we try to avoid filtering CUDA devices because ROCm also
